description.narrative:
The overall objective of the intervention is “to contribute, from civil society, to improve oversight of public administration in Colombia to make it more transparent, responsible and oriented towards peacebuilding and the common good”.
For achieving this goal, four specific objectives have been drawn up:
1. To advocate for increased transparency, responsibility and equality in the access to public administration;
2. To monitor the control exerted by the judicial system and independent control bodies over the exercise of public power in corruption cases;
3. To foster the appropriation of the public sphere by the citizenry and advocate for more effective protection mechanisms for whistleblowers, in particular those related to human rights’ violations;
4. To strengthen transparency and accountability in the implementation of the Peace Agreement.
